{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a53a077d-6f70-4e1f-943d-2ab18d3b6293","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"42bc7243-d134-4e69-8af0-19f846cf9985","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":154,"requestId":"9833:3B4A47:1ED018:28140A:69FFDDE6"},"id":"ec30bf86-e818-4f7c-a267-b968e8612dcc","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:22:50.521Z","parentId":"2a818752-a1b5-419a-ae94-464069122a99"}
